        <title>The South Secedes</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <section class="main-idea segment-opener" data-uuid="4ddd1937ce58436fbc1582bf0b5c2c33">
            <article data-uuid="094481c25e3e4c1297941b023ea56c96">
                <h4 data-uuid="62dd33318888426588d7b09b20cb9a1e">Main Idea</h4>
                <p class="main-idea" data-uuid="7742a6affb7a4d26956037707f70430f">The dispute over slavery led the South to secede.</p>
                <h2 data-uuid="1ca68a8f124c4a3381a58e0bb87d0fec">The South Secedes</h2>
                <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="c203083bdeb1439897d5db2631313d3b"></div>
            </article>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="0ffc5fc372b64bc5902bb9a4362421ca">Lincoln insisted that he would not change slavery in the South. However, he said that slavery could not expand and thus would eventually die out completely. That idea angered many southerners.<br />
        </p>
